This paper is about a programming language that includes a construct for reverse-mode differentiation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the mathematical notion of derivative and employs notions of differentiation familiar from real analysis, indicating that it may also be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA), software engineering (cs.SE), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
